name: NBCNews
text: LIVE: @NBCNews Special Report: George Floyd protests continue nationwide. https://t.co/ekIus2Kq9o

name: NBCNews
text: Video appears to show members of the National Guard in Minneapolis shooting paint canisters at residents sitting on their front porch. https://t.co/UrJJfVb1FL

name: NBCNews
text: BREAKING: Semi truck drives into a crowd of protesters on a bridge in Minneapolis, sending people running for safety; it doesn’t appear any protesters were hit by the truck, according to officials; truck driver was injured and is under arrest. https://t.co/NTWvyZbKdW

name: NBCNews
text:
RT @ReporterBlayne: Voices fill the air in downtown Atlanta:

“Say his name - George Floyd” https://t.co/fGtsvlXLSr

name: NBCNews
text: RT @ReporterBlayne: RIGHT NOW: Tear gas flying in downtown Atlanta. https://t.co/6kkWBFSeli

name: NBCNews
text: In the past several months, while most Americans have been ordered to shelter at home, US Immigration and Customs Enforcement has shuffled hundreds of people in its custody around the country, leading to COVID-19 outbreaks in facilities in multiple states. https://t.co/s9gbKFg9Z6

name: NBCNews
text: Washington, D.C., Mayor Bowser has ordered a citywide curfew Sunday night, as another wave of intense protests over the death of George Floyd enveloped the nation’s capital. https://t.co/2vgn09JLWe
